<title>UK: BA dips as report casts doubt on alliance.</title>
<headline>BA dips as report casts doubt on alliance.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>British Airways Plc shares dipped early on Friday after a report in the Guardian said its planned merger with American Airlines could ultimately be blocked by the British government and the European Commission.</p>
<p>The stock was down just 1p at 663 by 0811 GMT.</p>
<p>&quot;I'm not sure how reliable the report is but it could at be an excuse for some people to take profits,&quot; said one dealer.</p>
<p>The newspaper report quoted a senior European Commissioner as saying BA had failed so far to convince Brussels or the Office of Fair Trading that it could meet tough competition criteria.</p>
<p>It said it understood the OFT was demanding BA give up six percent of its landing slots at Heathrow but BA had offered only four percent, and that the Airline wanted to sell slots but that the Commission had ruled that illegal.</p>
<p>No-one at BA was immediately available for comment.</p>
<p>-- David Holmes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 4367</p>
